//github.com/titzer/virgil</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/lisdkp/virgil_fast_lightweight_native"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Sep 2021 13:49:44 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>How to deal with bugs in an agile setting</title><link>https://lobste.rs/s/6crquc/how_deal_with_bugs_agile_setting</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Even though we would all like to have bug free software, that is sadly hardly ever the case!
I’m curious about how other people tackle the burden of a constant trickle of bug reports (and if you don’t have that, congratulations on your eminent software development practices).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;How does your workplace deal with semi-urgent bugs and requests, that are important and small enough to be completed within a day or two?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In larger organizations it seems quite common to have each team spend one day of the week on these  types of issues, or having a rotating schedule. What’s your experience with these or other methods, pros and cons? What do you believe works best?&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Sep 2021 11:43:44 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Using 1Password 's `op` CLI tool exposes your secrets to other users on your system</title><link>https://twitter.com/grhmc/status/1443037314817695744</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/qpahty/using_1password_s_op_cli_tool_exposes_your"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Sep 2021 21:21:24 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>containers/youki: A container runtime written in Rust</title><link>https://github.com/containers/youki</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/l5mbvo/containers_youki_container_runtime"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Sep 2021 17:04:01 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Google and Facebook, I am facilitating packet filtering to block your tracking</title><link>https://peguero.xyz/blog/google_and_facebook_i_am_facilitating_packet_filtering_to_block_your_tracking.html</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/jpca2y/google_facebook_i_am_facilitating_packet"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 27 Sep 2021 20:22:57 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Gemini: the misaligned incentives</title><link>https://gerikson.com/blog/comm/Gemini-misaligned-incentives.html</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/3lqpko/gemini_misaligned_incentives"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Sep 2021 17:14:24 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>bc: An implementation of the POSIX bc calculator with GNU extensions and dc</title><link>https://github.com/gavinhoward/bc</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/l5qvp4/bc_implementatio