moon-was-full</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/ixowaa/code_worked_differently_when_moon_was"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Sep 2021 18:24:00 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Installing Void Linux with a Serial Terminal</title><link>https://battlepenguin.com/tech/installing-void-linux-with-a-serial-terminal</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/cb4b50/installing_void_linux_with_serial"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 27 Sep 2021 14:02:02 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>SQLime — Online  SQLite playground</title><link>https://sqlime.org/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/qdbovt/sqlime_online_sqlite_playground"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Sep 2021 08:28:05 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Inductive logic programming at 30: a new introduction</title><link>https://arxiv.org/pdf/2008.07912</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Inductive logic programming (ILP) is a form of machine learning. The goal of ILP is to induce a hypothesis (a set of logical rules) that generalises given training examples. In contrast to most forms of machine learning, ILP can learn human-readable hypotheses from small amounts of data. As ILP approaches 30, we provide a new introduction to the field. We introduce the necessary logical notation and the main ILP learning settings. We describe the main building blocks of an ILP system. We compare several ILP systems on several dimensions. We describe in detail four systems (Aleph, TILDE, ASPAL, and Metagol). We document some of the main application areas of ILP. Finally, we summarise the current limitations and outline promising directions for future research.&lt;/p&gt;

            &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/zq1oph/inductive_logic_programming_at_30_new"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Sep 2021 16:04:45 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Common Newbie Mistakes and Bad Practices in Rust: Bad Habits</title><link>https://adventures.michaelfbryan.com/posts/rust-best-practices/bad-habits/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/rzzet2/common_newbie_mistakes_bad_practices"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 27 Sep 2021 13:13:53 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Using rclone for Cloud to Cloud Transfer</title><link>https://www.rsync.net/resources/howto/rclone.html</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/lyaxrj/using_rclone_for_cloud_cloud_transfer"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Sep 2021 14:47:57 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>A Versioned Document Graph Database</title><link>https://github.com/GavinMendelGleason/why_terminusx</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/spad6n/versioned_document_graph_database"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Sep 2021 10:54:35 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Breaking pins to upgrade the CPU - The Thinkpad Quad-Core mod</title><link>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fs4GjDiOie8</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/5rgf6e/breaking_pins_upgrade_cpu_thinkpad_quad"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Sep 2021 15:47:14 -0500</pubDate></item></channel></rss>